  "texts": [
    "Like CrowdX, it is built using Unity3D and PersonX.",
    "It contains 10,000 video clips of five frames each, with a frame rate of 30 fps and a resolution of 1024×768.",
    "The average number of people per frame is 250.",
    "The pedestrians are randomly instantiated in the scene and move with direction and velocity that follow a Gaussian and a uniform distribution, respectively.",
    "Table 1 reports a summary of the main features of synthetic data sets, as well as the above-mentioned benchmark real data sets, for comparison, in terms of their number of images, pedestrian count and number of scenes."
